Diagnosis.
Apex of fastigium pointing (
Fig. 4
); fore femur with 2 dorsal inner subapical spurs (in addition to 1 dorsal inner apical spur, 
Fig. 21
); male X th abdominal tergite without gap between hooks (
Fig. 44
); male epiproct distal margin strait (
Fig. 44
); female subgenital plate triangular, obtuse (
Fig. 87
); tibia and distal part of femur brown (
Fig. 96
).

Description.
Apex of fastigium pointing (
Fig. 4
); fore femur with 2 dorsal inner subapical spurs (in addition to 1 dorsal inner apical spur, 
Fig. 21
); hind femur 3.3 
–
3.8 times as long as wide, with 10 
–
12 chevron ridges; hind tibia with 10 inner and 13 outer dorsal spines. Tibiae and distal part of femora brown (
Fig. 96
). 
Male.
X th abdominal tergite without gap between hooks, contact between the two lobes short for the genus (
Fig. 44
); paraprocts Sshaped, with a minute terminal (median) hook (
Fig. 69
); epiproct distal margin strait (
Fig. 44
). Epiphallic apodeme with anterior part tongue-shaped (side view, 
Fig. 67
); distal part with a single short inward projection (
Fig. 68
).

Female.
Subgenital plate short, triangular, distal margin obtuse (
Fig. 87
). Ovipositor of average size for the genus (
Fig. 86
).
